README

This folder contains 5 scripts used for the RNA sequence data:

Four of these were run on the crop diversity HPC:
#---------------------------------------------------#

1. Prepare_databases
This downloads the genomes for mapping against and builds them into hisat2 indexes. One index for the host and another index for host,phix and organelle. 
This was run in an interactive sesison. 

2. run_snakemake_preprocessing
This takes the RNA seq files from Novogene and concatenates those that were run over two sequencing lanes into a single file. 

3. RNA_preprocessing & RNA_preprocessing_config
This is a snakemake pipeline containing the filtering (fastp and sortmeRNA) and mapping of reads to the Hisat indexes. The config details the parameters use. 

4. Hisat-alignment-array-290426
This is an array script with the same parameters as in the snakemake pipeline and used in place of the hisat rules in that pipeline to speed up sample processing. 

One script was run downstream in R
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#

5. Create_RNA_SI_table
This parses the log files from the HPC scripts and gather the read counts and make a supplementary table 2.
